radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix appears distended up to 8 mm with surrounding fat stranding. No evidence of rupture or fluid collections, no free air or free fluid throughout the abdomen. Mild bibasilar atelectasis in the visualized portions of the lungs, otherwise clear lungs. The liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, bilateral adrenal glands, and bilateral kidneys are within normal limits. No mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy. The abdominal aorta is normal in caliber and contour. Bladder, distal ureters, uterus, ovaries, sigmoid colon, and rectum are within normal limits with no free fluid or free air throughout the pelvis.
